"", "similarity": null}, "passed": true}, "short_span_min_tokens": {"details": {"min_tokens": 2, "token_count": 164}, "passed": true}}, "text": "TAIPEI\n\nReference:\n\nTaipei, in reporting the 24 May riots observed that very few military or civil police were sent to the scene, and that the police made no positive efforts toward quelling the trouble, but instead seemed to give in to the violence of the mob. noted that the disturbance was carried on in a \"somewhat organized manner!\"\n\nabout a week before the riots, Vice President Chen Cheng, generally regarded as Chiang's probable successor, gave a speech in which he predicted that the American authorities would \"whitewash\" Sergeant Reynolds. He reportedly said that this was an example of how the United States forced China to accept its decisions, and that the United States must be shown that China would not be forced into following US policy. Chen had vetoed the use of troops in the early stages of the riot.\n\nThe situation in Taipei remains quiet, but martial law will remain in effect until the government feels assured that no further violence will occur", "token_count": 164, "token_end_0based": 167, "token_start_0based": 4, "token_text": "taipei reference taipei in reporting the 24 may riots observed that very few military or civil police were sent to the scene and that the police made no positive efforts toward quelling the trouble but instead seemed to give in to the violence of the mob noted that the disturbance was carried on in a somewhat organized manner about a week before the riots vice president chen cheng generally regarded as chiang's probable successor gave a speech in which he predicted that the american authorities would whitewash sergeant reynolds he reportedly said that this was an example of how the united states forced china to accept its decisions and that the united states must be shown that china would not be forced into following us policy chen had vetoed the use of troops in the early 